race.description: Ladbrokes Launceston Cup Packages On Sale Mdn
race.comment: TIMMIE LAD (7) was only beaten 1.3 lengths on debut over 1400m at this track when expected to need the outing. Draws inside again and has been kept on the fresh side. Darmanin is a key jockey switch replacing the apprentice. This is winnable with the extra fitness. DON TURBOAS (6) rates similarly on a narrow defeat at Hobart over 1200m heavily bet. Third up now, and is capable of making amends. MONCLERE (5) placed here over 1400m and is on a quick back-up. Must be pleasing and a senior hoop replaces the 3kg apprentice. Draws inside and can't be ruled out. ARCADE BOY (1) comes out of the same race and disappointed. Spiked his figures beaten a nose this track/trip prior. The in-form Byrne Burke stays aboard and he rates well enough to consider at good odds.
